  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Crisis Specific Appeals</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ireland&#x2019;s humanitarian response and funding is directed to where needs are greatest in sudden onset, protracted and conflict related crises, with a particular emphasis on forgotten and underfunded emergencies.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Under the Crisis Specific Appeals budget line, Ireland will continue in 2017 to respond to severe, large scale, humanitarian crises around the globe, and in particular in Africa and the Middle East. Ireland will also continue to focus on the most severe, large scale crises in the Middle East. Further support under this budget line is proposed for crises in the Lake Chad Basin and across the Sahel in 2017, building on humanitarian assistance provided in 2016. It is anticipated that funding of &#x20AC;2 million will be provided to the ICRC and UN partners working to support displaced communities affected by Boko Haram and food insecurity in the region. Under this budget line, Ireland will continue to focus on the most severe, large scale crises in the Middle East, in particular to the humanitarian crises caused by conflict and violence in Syria, Iraq and Yemen. It is proposed to allocate up to &#x20AC;10 million to the Syria crisis under this budget line. Also under this budget line, it is proposed to allocate 3 million each to the Yemen and Iraq CBPFs. Lastly, Ireland will provide funding to the humanitarian response to the refugee/IDP crisis in Bangladesh and Myanmar</narrative>
  </description>
